1
00:00:05,756 --> 00:00:11,845
♪

2
00:00:13,388 --> 00:01:42,060
♪

3
00:01:45,981 --> 00:01:48,483
(helicopter droning)

4
00:01:50,152 --> 00:01:52,029
All right, fill me in.

5
00:01:52,029 --> 00:01:54,072
The main unit's
assembled at point zero.

6
00:01:54,072 --> 00:01:56,241
All personnel
are standing by.

7
00:01:56,241 --> 00:01:58,327
(droning)

8
00:01:58,327 --> 00:01:59,828
Behemoth, huh?

9
00:01:59,828 --> 00:02:02,497
This'll be our first
big catch in a while.

10
00:02:02,497 --> 00:02:05,000
(droning)

11
00:02:08,378 --> 00:02:13,759
♪

12
00:02:13,759 --> 00:02:16,970
(grunting)

13
00:02:16,970 --> 00:02:19,264
Don't fuck with me,

14
00:02:19,264 --> 00:02:23,101
you piece of shit!

15
00:02:23,101 --> 00:02:25,354
♪

16
00:02:25,354 --> 00:02:27,189
Ultimate technique.

17
00:02:27,189 --> 00:02:29,858
Tornado hammer!

18
00:02:29,858 --> 00:02:31,443
Look, they're holding hands.

19
00:02:31,443 --> 00:02:33,570
I mean, that punch
can shatter concrete

20
00:02:33,570 --> 00:02:35,322
and he blocked it
with one hand!

21
00:02:35,322 --> 00:02:37,115
Calm down, Mitsuro, all right?

22
00:02:37,115 --> 00:02:37,991
That's enough.

23
00:02:37,991 --> 00:02:39,618
Have you forgotten
what I taught you?

24
00:02:39,618 --> 00:02:42,913
The first to lose his cool is
the first to lose the fight.

25
00:02:42,913 --> 00:02:45,457
Akira.

26
00:02:45,457 --> 00:02:47,626
Was that some kind of
trick with your hand?

27
00:02:47,626 --> 00:02:49,127
The gloves, maybe?

28
00:02:49,127 --> 00:02:50,253
Hm.

29
00:02:50,253 --> 00:02:52,214
You know, it's funny,
but I guess we've never met

30
00:02:52,214 --> 00:02:53,799
face to face before,

31
00:02:53,799 --> 00:02:56,343
but I've heard all
about you from Simca.

32
00:02:56,343 --> 00:02:57,344
Simca, huh?

33
00:02:57,344 --> 00:02:58,220
Oh, that's cool.

34
00:02:58,220 --> 00:03:01,139
So I guess you two
are friends, huh?

35
00:03:02,641 --> 00:03:05,477
(zapping)

36
00:03:05,477 --> 00:03:08,146
(grunting)

37
00:03:08,146 --> 00:03:11,441
You cocky punk.

38
00:03:11,441 --> 00:03:13,318
Ah!

39
00:03:13,318 --> 00:03:15,570
Hm.

40
00:03:15,570 --> 00:03:17,989
(shouts)

41
00:03:17,989 --> 00:03:20,033
I don't care how many
of you there are.

42
00:03:20,033 --> 00:03:22,703
I'll send you all back to the
garbage heap you came from.

43
00:03:22,703 --> 00:03:24,496
(shouting)

44
00:03:24,496 --> 00:03:25,539
Ikki!

45
00:03:25,539 --> 00:03:28,417
No, this is too
terrible to watch,

46
00:03:28,417 --> 00:03:30,752
and yet I can't
tear my eyes away.

47
00:03:30,752 --> 00:03:32,712
(laughing)

48
00:03:34,089 --> 00:03:35,882
I can't believe
he fell for that.

49
00:03:35,882 --> 00:03:38,301
You dumbass, do you even
know what you're doing?

50
00:03:38,301 --> 00:03:40,470
Hey, guys, shh, shh.

51
00:03:42,180 --> 00:03:44,474
Damn, if they hadn't
blown my cover,

52
00:03:44,474 --> 00:03:47,102
I would've drop‐kicked you
in the back of the head.

53
00:03:47,102 --> 00:03:49,062
So how do you like
my new technique?

54
00:03:49,062 --> 00:03:51,273
I call it "body double."

55
00:03:51,273 --> 00:03:54,109
♪

56
00:03:54,109 --> 00:03:56,319
(shouting)

57
00:03:56,319 --> 00:03:58,989
Now you're gonna pay!

58
00:03:58,989 --> 00:04:01,032
(grunting)

59
00:04:01,032 --> 00:04:02,951
No way.

60
00:04:04,244 --> 00:04:05,454
(chuckles)

61
00:04:05,454 --> 00:04:07,747
You may have blocked
his punch with one hand,

62
00:04:07,747 --> 00:04:10,625
but I did it without
using a single finger.

63
00:04:10,625 --> 00:04:12,878
I'd say that
makes me the winner.

64
00:04:12,878 --> 00:04:15,505
(rumbling)

65
00:04:18,216 --> 00:04:21,052
Cut the bullshit and
use your ATs, dammit!

66
00:04:21,052 --> 00:04:24,389
This is about to get serious.

67
00:04:24,389 --> 00:04:27,559
(roaring)

68
00:04:31,271 --> 00:04:34,524
His aura is so strong
you can almost feel it.

69
00:04:34,524 --> 00:04:36,568
I see why they
call him Behemoth.

70
00:04:36,568 --> 00:04:40,655
In the age of gods, humans,
beasts, fish, and plants

71
00:04:40,655 --> 00:04:43,450
all lived together
in the same place.

72
00:04:43,450 --> 00:04:45,452
But that world couldn't last.

73
00:04:45,452 --> 00:04:48,413
The fish ate the plants,
the birds ate the fish,

74
00:04:48,413 --> 00:04:49,998
the beasts ate the birds.

75
00:04:49,998 --> 00:04:51,792
So the gods said
to the beasts,

76
00:04:51,792 --> 00:04:53,210
"Scatter to the fields.

77
00:04:53,210 --> 00:04:54,961
The birds will
take to the sky

78
00:04:54,961 --> 00:04:56,922
and the fish to the sea."

79
00:04:56,922 --> 00:05:00,133
Mayan legend.

80
00:05:00,133 --> 00:05:03,136
Akira told me that story
just after we met.

81
00:05:03,136 --> 00:05:06,306
I remember that day in the
park as if it were yesterday.

82
00:05:06,306 --> 00:05:08,600
Hold on a second,
is this story gonna be long?

83
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:11,102
'Cause I kind of need to
change clothes right now.

84
00:05:11,102 --> 00:05:13,021
That was before
he formed Behemoth

85
00:05:13,021 --> 00:05:14,231
and became the
King of Beasts.

86
00:05:14,231 --> 00:05:16,942
Not a flashback.

87
00:05:16,942 --> 00:05:19,444
(birds chirping)

88
00:05:19,444 --> 00:05:21,530
(birds cooing)

89
00:05:23,073 --> 00:05:25,575
So you like birds, huh?

90
00:05:27,202 --> 00:05:29,287
You must be Simca.

91
00:05:29,287 --> 00:05:33,542
Well, Spitfire already
told me about the plan.

92
00:05:33,542 --> 00:05:34,793
(gasping)

93
00:05:34,793 --> 00:05:37,838
I like coming to this park
when the doves are molting.

94
00:05:37,838 --> 00:05:39,506
Their new feathers
are easy to break

95
00:05:39,506 --> 00:05:41,633
and have thick
veins inside them.

96
00:05:41,633 --> 00:05:43,301
Take a look.

97
00:05:43,301 --> 00:05:46,221
If they try to fly
with broken wings,

98
00:05:46,221 --> 00:05:48,306
then they force
out the blood

99
00:05:48,306 --> 00:05:50,809
and it rains from the sky.

100
00:05:50,809 --> 00:05:52,394
I'll take the job.

101
00:05:52,394 --> 00:05:53,979
It's the duty of
beasts like me

102
00:05:53,979 --> 00:05:55,605
to break the wings
of the little birds

103
00:05:55,605 --> 00:05:58,483
that think they can
soar into C‐class.

104
00:05:58,483 --> 00:06:00,068
You know something?

105
00:06:00,068 --> 00:06:01,486
I really hate birds.

106
00:06:01,486 --> 00:06:03,321
(engine revving)

107
00:06:03,321 --> 00:06:06,491
They're always looking down
on me from up in the sky.

108
00:06:07,868 --> 00:06:10,453
But once I break their wings,

109
00:06:10,453 --> 00:06:12,581
they just writhe
on the ground

110
00:06:12,581 --> 00:06:14,916
like pathetic little worms.

111
00:06:16,334 --> 00:06:17,711
This is his stage.

112
00:06:17,711 --> 00:06:20,380
This is where the gods have
willed him to do battle.

113
00:06:20,380 --> 00:06:22,674
But no matter how
long his Fangs are,

114
00:06:22,674 --> 00:06:24,759
they still can't
reach the sky.

115
00:06:24,759 --> 00:06:27,012
(grunting)

116
00:06:27,012 --> 00:06:30,056
♪

117
00:06:30,056 --> 00:06:31,474
Wow, our spur‐of‐the‐moment

118
00:06:31,474 --> 00:06:33,518
combo attack actually
worked pretty well.

119
00:06:33,518 --> 00:06:34,895
I guess that proves
once and for all

120
00:06:34,895 --> 00:06:36,855
that I'm the greatest genius
the world has ever known.

121
00:06:36,855 --> 00:06:39,900
Well, I have to admit
that wasn't bad.

122
00:06:39,900 --> 00:06:43,069
♪

123
00:06:43,069 --> 00:06:45,655
(heavy breathing)

124
00:06:45,655 --> 00:06:50,577
♪

125
00:06:50,577 --> 00:06:52,454
You don't have
to take that crap!

126
00:06:52,454 --> 00:06:55,707
Show him what the
Fang King is made of.

127
00:06:55,707 --> 00:06:59,794
Now he has to face his
greatest weakness, the sky.

128
00:06:59,794 --> 00:07:03,340
♪

129
00:07:03,340 --> 00:07:05,967
(exploding)

130
00:07:05,967 --> 00:07:08,303
Now, that's more like it!

131
00:07:08,303 --> 00:07:09,554
Watch out, Akira!

132
00:07:09,554 --> 00:07:10,805
It's a trap!

133
00:07:10,805 --> 00:07:11,973
Ah!

134
00:07:11,973 --> 00:07:14,184
Wonder how many times
he'll fall for that.

135
00:07:14,184 --> 00:07:16,144
(smacking)

136
00:07:16,144 --> 00:07:20,065
Looks like this is turning
into a pretty one‐sided match.

137
00:07:20,065 --> 00:07:21,733
Oh!

138
00:07:21,733 --> 00:07:23,902
Ohh!

139
00:07:23,902 --> 00:07:25,487
Oh, man, this is for real?

140
00:07:25,487 --> 00:07:26,905
Are we really gonna
win this thing?

141
00:07:26,905 --> 00:07:29,532
Now that the Crow has
brought the sky to the Cube,

142
00:07:29,532 --> 00:07:31,284
his combination
attack is making

143
00:07:31,284 --> 00:07:32,911
minced meat out of Akira!

144
00:07:32,911 --> 00:07:35,372
I hate to say it, but it
looks like these rookies

145
00:07:35,372 --> 00:07:38,416
are roasting up some
Behemoth for dinner.

146
00:07:38,416 --> 00:07:39,250
Come on, Crow!

147
00:07:39,250 --> 00:07:40,543
We've got the edge now!

148
00:07:40,543 --> 00:07:42,587
Let's finish him in one shot.

149
00:07:42,587 --> 00:07:44,881
(gasping)

150
00:07:44,881 --> 00:07:46,841
♪

151
00:07:46,841 --> 00:07:48,385
(grunting)

152
00:07:48,385 --> 00:07:51,471
What the hell do you think
you're doing, Akira?

153
00:07:51,471 --> 00:07:53,223
You have our pride
on your back!

154
00:07:53,223 --> 00:07:55,475
The emblems of over
a thousand Behemoths

155
00:07:55,475 --> 00:07:56,351
are riding on you.

156
00:07:56,351 --> 00:07:57,519
Don't cower on the ground

157
00:07:57,519 --> 00:08:01,022
like some kind of
pathetic rodent!

158
00:08:02,607 --> 00:08:07,112
♪

159
00:08:07,112 --> 00:08:09,447
(gasping)

160
00:08:09,447 --> 00:08:11,908
♪

161
00:08:11,908 --> 00:08:13,284
(yells)

162
00:08:13,284 --> 00:08:15,328
Crow, attack from
the right side!

163
00:08:15,328 --> 00:08:18,915
Who said you could
tell me what to do?

164
00:08:18,915 --> 00:08:21,126
Whoa!

165
00:08:21,126 --> 00:08:23,795
‐That's bull‐‐
‐Shit, brilliant.

166
00:08:23,795 --> 00:08:25,505
They don't call him
the King of Beasts

167
00:08:25,505 --> 00:08:26,840
for nothing, after all.

168
00:08:26,840 --> 00:08:29,300
(whooshing)

169
00:08:29,300 --> 00:08:30,552
Spank me silly!

170
00:08:30,552 --> 00:08:32,804
What the hell's
going on in there?

171
00:08:32,804 --> 00:08:35,014
Ah!

172
00:08:37,183 --> 00:08:39,853
(whirring)

173
00:08:39,853 --> 00:08:42,814
(whooshing)

174
00:08:42,814 --> 00:08:43,606
Fuck.

175
00:08:43,606 --> 00:08:44,482
You were right.

176
00:08:44,482 --> 00:08:46,901
This is turning into
a one‐sided match.

177
00:08:46,901 --> 00:08:47,736
Told ya.

178
00:08:47,736 --> 00:08:49,404
I am the Fang,

179
00:08:49,404 --> 00:08:50,572
the king of destruction

180
00:08:50,572 --> 00:08:53,158
who tears through
everything in his path.

181
00:08:53,158 --> 00:08:56,202
Bloody armor, come forth!

182
00:08:57,328 --> 00:08:59,414
(groaning)

183
00:08:59,414 --> 00:09:05,837
♪

184
00:09:05,837 --> 00:09:08,298
(gasping)

185
00:09:09,507 --> 00:09:11,134
Can you hear it?

186
00:09:11,134 --> 00:09:13,136
The Regalia is howling.

187
00:09:13,136 --> 00:09:19,726
♪

188
00:09:19,726 --> 00:09:21,936
(screaming)

189
00:09:21,936 --> 00:09:29,486
♪

190
00:09:33,323 --> 00:09:38,036
♪

191
00:09:38,036 --> 00:09:40,038
Come on.

192
00:09:40,038 --> 00:09:42,415
(screaming)

193
00:09:45,335 --> 00:09:46,503
Ohh!

194
00:09:46,503 --> 00:09:47,962
‐Ahh!
‐Ohh!

195
00:09:47,962 --> 00:09:49,631
Ahh!

196
00:09:51,925 --> 00:09:54,427
The great beast
has descended!

197
00:09:54,427 --> 00:09:56,638
And I gotta tell ya,
this is the first time

198
00:09:56,638 --> 00:10:00,558
I've ever seen Akira
break out the Fang Regalia!

199
00:10:00,558 --> 00:10:02,268
Ah!

200
00:10:04,896 --> 00:10:07,232
Son of a bitch!

201
00:10:07,232 --> 00:10:08,900
Hey, Crow, you all right?

202
00:10:08,900 --> 00:10:12,362
Hell yeah!

203
00:10:12,362 --> 00:10:14,280
That's great.

204
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:16,616
That's so cool that
he, like, transformed!

205
00:10:16,616 --> 00:10:17,575
Mine don't do that!

206
00:10:17,575 --> 00:10:19,911
I want a pair like yours!

207
00:10:19,911 --> 00:10:22,163
Come on, man,
hook a brother up.

208
00:10:22,163 --> 00:10:24,582
♪

209
00:10:24,582 --> 00:10:29,587
Ha, but I guess you won't
hand 'em over for free, right?

210
00:10:29,587 --> 00:10:31,131
That's fine.

211
00:10:31,131 --> 00:10:34,175
I'll just take them.

212
00:10:34,175 --> 00:10:35,760
I guess you
haven't noticed yet,

213
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:37,595
but your sky is gone

214
00:10:37,595 --> 00:10:41,057
and your wings
are broken, Crow.

215
00:10:41,057 --> 00:10:43,268
The cage is
closed once again.

216
00:10:43,268 --> 00:10:46,604
From now on, you're
trapped in a world of beasts.

217
00:10:46,604 --> 00:10:49,858
♪

218
00:10:49,858 --> 00:10:52,569
It's hard to say exactly
what Ikki's up against.

219
00:10:52,569 --> 00:10:54,487
Even though I inherited
Rika's position

220
00:10:54,487 --> 00:10:55,822
as one of the eight kings,

221
00:10:55,822 --> 00:10:57,031
I still don't
know all that much

222
00:10:57,031 --> 00:10:59,284
about all the different
Regalia out there.

223
00:10:59,284 --> 00:11:00,785
Judging by Akira's attacks,

224
00:11:00,785 --> 00:11:02,787
it's probably
not a single part,

225
00:11:02,787 --> 00:11:04,956
but an entire
system of operation.

226
00:11:04,956 --> 00:11:07,625
It seems to collect inertia
from braking and landing,

227
00:11:07,625 --> 00:11:10,837
then retransmit it as
a kind of energy wave.

228
00:11:10,837 --> 00:11:12,213
If you look at it that way,

229
00:11:12,213 --> 00:11:14,674
it makes sense that
Akira can't fly very well.

230
00:11:14,674 --> 00:11:17,010
Considering that he's got
such a complex mechanism

231
00:11:17,010 --> 00:11:18,636
in such a tiny wheel space,

232
00:11:18,636 --> 00:11:22,473
it's no wonder that he has
to sacrifice other functions.

233
00:11:24,309 --> 00:11:25,935
He's thrown them away.

234
00:11:25,935 --> 00:11:29,939
In exchange for Fangs,
he's given up his wings.

235
00:11:29,939 --> 00:11:32,108
(shouting)

236
00:11:32,108 --> 00:11:34,068
This is starting to get ugly.

237
00:11:34,068 --> 00:11:35,653
I should be all right,
but at this rate,

238
00:11:35,653 --> 00:11:37,363
I'm afraid shark boy
isn't gonna be able

239
00:11:37,363 --> 00:11:39,324
to hold out much longer.

240
00:11:39,324 --> 00:11:44,037
♪

241
00:11:44,037 --> 00:11:46,372
Could it be‐‐above us?

242
00:11:46,372 --> 00:11:49,500
(grunting)

243
00:11:49,500 --> 00:11:51,669
Didn't I tell you?

244
00:11:51,669 --> 00:11:55,548
♪

245
00:11:55,548 --> 00:11:58,218
You're trapped in my cage.

246
00:11:58,218 --> 00:12:00,637
You can't escape.

247
00:12:00,637 --> 00:12:02,680
This is my world now.

248
00:12:02,680 --> 00:12:05,183
There is no sky.

249
00:12:05,183 --> 00:12:07,227
Oh, you got told!

250
00:12:07,227 --> 00:12:09,354
Now all that's left is
for these birdbrains

251
00:12:09,354 --> 00:12:10,688
to have their
heads chopped off

252
00:12:10,688 --> 00:12:13,316
like my grandma's chickens.

253
00:12:13,316 --> 00:12:15,985
Son of a bitch.

254
00:12:15,985 --> 00:12:17,862
What do we have to do
to beat that thing?

255
00:12:17,862 --> 00:12:19,197
Look, he always speeds up

256
00:12:19,197 --> 00:12:21,199
before he uses his
technique, right?

257
00:12:21,199 --> 00:12:22,700
Yeah, so what?

258
00:12:22,700 --> 00:12:24,535
Those giant Fang
attacks are created

259
00:12:24,535 --> 00:12:26,287
from the energy
made when he brakes,

260
00:12:26,287 --> 00:12:28,414
meaning the longer
and faster he rides,

261
00:12:28,414 --> 00:12:30,833
the bigger and more
powerful his attacks become.

262
00:12:30,833 --> 00:12:31,960
So if we stick to him,

263
00:12:31,960 --> 00:12:33,544
we can stop him
from picking up speed

264
00:12:33,544 --> 00:12:35,546
and he won't be able to
use his Fang technique.

265
00:12:35,546 --> 00:12:38,216
Well, why the hell didn't
you tell me that sooner,

266
00:12:38,216 --> 00:12:40,260
friggin' dumb‐‐oh!

267
00:12:40,260 --> 00:12:43,221
You're the dumbass, dumbass!

268
00:12:43,221 --> 00:12:44,597
They make a good team.

269
00:12:44,597 --> 00:12:46,557
You get the Fang
from far away,

270
00:12:46,557 --> 00:12:49,310
but if you move in close,
you get the hammer.

271
00:12:49,310 --> 00:12:52,897
The fight turned out just
how Spitfire said it would.

272
00:12:52,897 --> 00:12:56,025
It looks like I can't let
my guard down around him.

273
00:12:57,235 --> 00:12:59,404
Welcome back.

274
00:12:59,404 --> 00:13:01,072
You don't look very cheery.

275
00:13:01,072 --> 00:13:03,199
It's not a bad match, I guess,

276
00:13:03,199 --> 00:13:06,911
considering Ikki made Akira
break out the Fang Regalia.

277
00:13:06,911 --> 00:13:10,540
♪

278
00:13:10,540 --> 00:13:12,333
But maybe that's the problem.

279
00:13:12,333 --> 00:13:15,712
Akira just doesn't seem to be
enjoying himself tonight.

280
00:13:15,712 --> 00:13:18,464
If he's not having fun,
it's just boring.

281
00:13:18,464 --> 00:13:20,091
The stronger the opponent,

282
00:13:20,091 --> 00:13:22,885
the more interesting that
makes the battle, right?

283
00:13:22,885 --> 00:13:25,555
Normally, when a rider goes
all out, he's so excited

284
00:13:25,555 --> 00:13:28,141
it's like he has lightning
coursing through his veins.

285
00:13:28,141 --> 00:13:31,144
At least that's how
it's supposed to be.

286
00:13:31,144 --> 00:13:39,902
♪

287
00:13:39,902 --> 00:13:42,780
Akira's strength is
different than Ikki's.

288
00:13:42,780 --> 00:13:43,865
(beep)

289
00:13:43,865 --> 00:13:46,451
He had to sacrifice a lot
more than just his wings

290
00:13:46,451 --> 00:13:48,494
to get those Fangs.

291
00:13:48,494 --> 00:13:49,871
(beep)

292
00:13:49,871 --> 00:13:51,998
♪

293
00:13:51,998 --> 00:13:54,083
He didn't just lose
his love of fighting.

294
00:13:54,083 --> 00:13:56,627
He lost the only
friend he's ever had.

295
00:13:58,212 --> 00:14:00,298
These bastards are
illegal immigrants

296
00:14:00,298 --> 00:14:01,632
and AT smugglers.

297
00:14:01,632 --> 00:14:03,801
Fire on sight.

298
00:14:03,801 --> 00:14:05,762
(honking)

299
00:14:07,305 --> 00:14:09,807
(guns firing)

300
00:14:09,807 --> 00:14:11,476
Damn.

301
00:14:11,476 --> 00:14:14,979
Don't let them
get away, Akira.

302
00:14:14,979 --> 00:14:17,023
You hear that,
don't fuck this up.

303
00:14:17,023 --> 00:14:20,276
Who the hell do you
think you're talking to?

304
00:14:20,276 --> 00:14:22,779
(beeping)

305
00:14:22,779 --> 00:14:25,782
(whooshing)

306
00:14:28,951 --> 00:14:30,787
Agh!

307
00:14:32,747 --> 00:14:35,583
Looks like they're
wrapping up down there.

308
00:14:35,583 --> 00:14:37,335
(gasping)

309
00:14:39,128 --> 00:14:41,130
Huh?

310
00:14:45,718 --> 00:14:46,677
Not good!

311
00:14:46,677 --> 00:14:48,513
He's gonna try to take
that girl hostage.

312
00:14:48,513 --> 00:14:50,556
Ah!

313
00:14:50,556 --> 00:15:03,236
♪

314
00:15:03,236 --> 00:15:05,571
(heavy breathing)

315
00:15:05,571 --> 00:15:14,539
♪

316
00:15:14,539 --> 00:15:16,040
Are you all right?

317
00:15:16,040 --> 00:15:17,959
I'm sorry you
had to see that,

318
00:15:17,959 --> 00:15:20,294
but I was afraid he
was going to hurt you.

319
00:15:20,294 --> 00:15:22,547
Big brother!

320
00:15:22,547 --> 00:15:24,173
Please, hold on!

321
00:15:24,173 --> 00:15:25,842
Don't die.

322
00:15:25,842 --> 00:15:29,095
I‐‐I thought he was
going to take you hostage.

323
00:15:30,555 --> 00:15:31,889
He looked like
he was smuggling

324
00:15:31,889 --> 00:15:34,600
something in that box.

325
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:37,395
(chirping)

326
00:15:37,395 --> 00:15:39,021
(gasping)

327
00:15:39,021 --> 00:15:42,400
Why, my brother didn't
want to hurt anyone.

328
00:15:42,400 --> 00:15:44,777
That was just a present!

329
00:15:44,777 --> 00:15:46,737
Today is my birthday.

330
00:15:46,737 --> 00:15:48,531
My leg doesn't work,

331
00:15:48,531 --> 00:15:51,701
so he got me
something that could fly.

332
00:15:51,701 --> 00:15:57,331
♪

333
00:15:57,331 --> 00:15:58,332
I'm sorry.

334
00:15:58,332 --> 00:15:59,584
I really am.

335
00:15:59,584 --> 00:16:00,751
It's all right.

336
00:16:00,751 --> 00:16:02,253
He managed to pull through,

337
00:16:02,253 --> 00:16:03,796
and even though
he was my brother,

338
00:16:03,796 --> 00:16:05,548
he's still a criminal.

339
00:16:05,548 --> 00:16:07,925
Now, he's been
sent back home,

340
00:16:07,925 --> 00:16:10,219
but that's all behind me.

341
00:16:10,219 --> 00:16:11,262
I'm not mad.

342
00:16:11,262 --> 00:16:14,182
Actually, I want to
thank you for what you did.

343
00:16:14,182 --> 00:16:15,600
Thank me?

344
00:16:15,600 --> 00:16:17,018
But why, I just‐‐

345
00:16:17,018 --> 00:16:19,228
Because with my
leg the way it is,

346
00:16:19,228 --> 00:16:21,189
I've always dreamt of flying.

347
00:16:21,189 --> 00:16:22,773
I think it's
wonderful that ATs

348
00:16:22,773 --> 00:16:24,567
can make that
dream come true.

349
00:16:24,567 --> 00:16:27,528
You're able to use your
ATs to help fight crime.

350
00:16:27,528 --> 00:16:30,156
Really, I think that's great.

351
00:16:30,156 --> 00:16:33,409
It's, uh, nothing really.

352
00:16:33,409 --> 00:16:40,583
♪

353
00:16:40,583 --> 00:16:41,876
Fuck.

354
00:16:41,876 --> 00:16:44,503
♪

355
00:16:44,503 --> 00:16:46,631
(engine puttering)

356
00:16:46,631 --> 00:16:53,930
♪

357
00:16:53,930 --> 00:16:56,682
(bird chirping)

358
00:16:56,682 --> 00:16:58,684
Here you go, it's dinnertime.

359
00:16:58,684 --> 00:17:00,269
Open wide.

360
00:17:00,269 --> 00:17:01,520
What happened?

361
00:17:01,520 --> 00:17:03,981
Where are its wings?

362
00:17:03,981 --> 00:17:05,650
Oh, I chopped them off.

363
00:17:05,650 --> 00:17:07,485
If it had wings,
it would fly away.

364
00:17:07,485 --> 00:17:11,239
Now I don't have to worry
about it leaving me behind.

365
00:17:11,239 --> 00:17:13,157
♪

366
00:17:13,157 --> 00:17:15,743
(engine puttering)

367
00:17:15,743 --> 00:17:19,121
♪

368
00:17:19,121 --> 00:17:21,290
(cheering)

369
00:17:21,290 --> 00:17:24,001
♪

370
00:17:24,001 --> 00:17:25,002
Believe it or not,

371
00:17:25,002 --> 00:17:28,005
someone has challenged
Agito for his Regalia!

372
00:17:28,005 --> 00:17:30,633
Will this be the end of
the Fang King's reign?

373
00:17:30,633 --> 00:17:32,802
Let's see who he's up against.

374
00:17:32,802 --> 00:17:47,149
♪

375
00:17:47,149 --> 00:17:50,111
Ren!

376
00:17:50,111 --> 00:17:51,237
Just what the
hell's going on?

377
00:17:51,237 --> 00:17:52,530
I don't understand.

378
00:17:52,530 --> 00:17:54,198
Don't you try to stop me.

379
00:17:54,198 --> 00:17:55,533
I am the one who set this up.

380
00:17:55,533 --> 00:17:58,077
Agito just accepted
my challenge.

381
00:17:58,077 --> 00:18:00,997
Dumbass, why don't you try
thinking with your brain

382
00:18:00,997 --> 00:18:02,999
instead of your
balls for once?

383
00:18:02,999 --> 00:18:04,875
Don't you see,
she's been using you

384
00:18:04,875 --> 00:18:06,836
just to get at
the Fang Regalia.

385
00:18:06,836 --> 00:18:08,754
(gasping)

386
00:18:08,754 --> 00:18:10,172
When my brother came here,

387
00:18:10,172 --> 00:18:12,925
he was an underground
AT parts broker.

388
00:18:12,925 --> 00:18:15,052
Before he got deported,
he was trying to steal

389
00:18:15,052 --> 00:18:17,221
the Fang Regalia for
one of his clients.

390
00:18:17,221 --> 00:18:20,141
Now he's receiving threats
from other smugglers.

391
00:18:20,141 --> 00:18:22,435
I'm afraid he's
in over his head.

392
00:18:22,435 --> 00:18:23,561
That's why I'm here.

393
00:18:23,561 --> 00:18:26,564
I need the Fang Regalia
to save my brother's life.

394
00:18:26,564 --> 00:18:27,565
I'm sorry.

395
00:18:27,565 --> 00:18:30,401
I was using you to find
out Agito's weak point.

396
00:18:30,401 --> 00:18:33,404
Please forgive me,
I had no choice.

397
00:18:37,325 --> 00:18:39,410
Straight from
the horse's mouth.

398
00:18:39,410 --> 00:18:41,579
I bet you feel pretty
stupid right now.

399
00:18:41,579 --> 00:18:42,872
I'm going to fly!

400
00:18:42,872 --> 00:18:45,416
You'll see!

401
00:18:45,416 --> 00:18:48,586
I'll win, and I'll
fly all the way home.

402
00:18:48,586 --> 00:18:50,296
Just wait.

403
00:18:50,296 --> 00:18:56,927
♪

404
00:18:56,927 --> 00:18:59,430
Sometimes,
on days like these,

405
00:18:59,430 --> 00:19:01,932
I feel like even I can fly,

406
00:19:01,932 --> 00:19:04,894
even if only for a moment.

407
00:19:04,894 --> 00:19:08,230
♪

408
00:19:08,230 --> 00:19:09,398
Yeah.

409
00:19:09,398 --> 00:19:15,655
♪

410
00:19:15,655 --> 00:19:18,282
(swooshing)

411
00:19:18,282 --> 00:19:21,410
It hurts when I
get sand in there.

412
00:19:21,410 --> 00:19:26,332
I can't run fast enough to
keep up with you anymore.

413
00:19:26,332 --> 00:19:27,792
(sighing)

414
00:19:27,792 --> 00:19:30,544
They say anyone can fly
if they try hard enough,

415
00:19:30,544 --> 00:19:32,838
but that's not true.

416
00:19:32,838 --> 00:19:34,632
Birds that fly
with broken wings

417
00:19:34,632 --> 00:19:37,134
will fall to their deaths.

418
00:19:37,134 --> 00:19:39,970
But if I can pretend to
fly for a little while,

419
00:19:39,970 --> 00:19:42,682
at least I won't
be left behind.

420
00:19:42,682 --> 00:19:44,600
I'm sorry.

421
00:19:46,185 --> 00:19:49,313
I'm sorry.

422
00:19:49,313 --> 00:20:01,867
♪

423
00:20:01,867 --> 00:20:04,120
You don't have to fly.

424
00:20:04,120 --> 00:20:07,957
♪

425
00:20:07,957 --> 00:20:09,041
Akira.

426
00:20:09,041 --> 00:20:12,086
If you have to cry until
there are no more tears,

427
00:20:12,086 --> 00:20:14,839
if you have to carry
feathers drenched in blood,

428
00:20:14,839 --> 00:20:18,134
if you have to sacrifice
yourself to reach the sky,

429
00:20:18,134 --> 00:20:21,971
then you don't have to fly,
not in a sky like that.

430
00:20:21,971 --> 00:20:26,142
I promise I'll never fly
away and leave you behind.

431
00:20:26,142 --> 00:20:29,228
I'll stay with you
inside this cage.

432
00:20:32,982 --> 00:20:35,901
Is this really what you want?

433
00:20:35,901 --> 00:20:38,112
Is this what it's come to?

434
00:20:38,112 --> 00:20:40,990
♪

435
00:20:40,990 --> 00:20:43,909
Akira!

436
00:20:45,286 --> 00:20:46,912
I'm taking the Regalia.

437
00:20:46,912 --> 00:20:47,913
You hear me?

438
00:20:47,913 --> 00:20:49,999
(grunting)

439
00:20:49,999 --> 00:20:51,834
(clinking)

440
00:20:51,834 --> 00:20:54,044
(cheering)

441
00:20:54,044 --> 00:21:04,889
♪

442
00:21:04,889 --> 00:21:07,475
(cheering)

443
00:21:07,475 --> 00:21:10,311
If I were her, I would've
done the same thing.

444
00:21:10,311 --> 00:21:11,687
After what he's been through,

445
00:21:11,687 --> 00:21:13,731
I'm sure Akira is
quite proud of the fact

446
00:21:13,731 --> 00:21:15,024
that he can't fly.

447
00:21:15,024 --> 00:21:18,027
But, now, that pride
has turned to hate.

448
00:21:18,027 --> 00:21:20,237
All he cares about
is clipping the wings

449
00:21:20,237 --> 00:21:22,948
of those who fly above him.

450
00:21:27,077 --> 00:21:29,580
(cheering)

451
00:21:34,376 --> 00:21:36,295
That was amazing, Akira.

452
00:21:36,295 --> 00:21:38,255
You really are the king.

453
00:21:38,255 --> 00:21:39,799
(gasping)

454
00:21:39,799 --> 00:21:44,303
♪

455
00:21:44,303 --> 00:21:46,096
The strain from
using the Fang attack

456
00:21:46,096 --> 00:21:48,516
is tearing apart the
muscles on his legs.

457
00:21:48,516 --> 00:21:50,267
Akira?

458
00:21:50,267 --> 00:21:51,811
I'll finish this soon.

459
00:21:51,811 --> 00:21:53,646
Don't worry.

460
00:21:53,646 --> 00:21:55,481
Agito?

461
00:21:55,481 --> 00:21:57,566
I'm starting to get
sick of these guys.

462
00:21:57,566 --> 00:21:59,151
Let's finish this.

463
00:21:59,151 --> 00:22:02,279
This is the final trick.

464
00:22:02,279 --> 00:22:04,698
(shouting)

465
00:22:04,698 --> 00:22:26,971
♪

466
00:22:26,971 --> 00:22:28,722
♪ The truth ♪

467
00:22:28,722 --> 00:22:30,307
♪ The truth ♪

468
00:22:30,307 --> 00:22:32,560
♪ The truth shall
set you free ♪

469
00:22:32,560 --> 00:23:11,807
♪

470
00:23:11,807 --> 00:23:13,350
♪ Truth ♪

471
00:23:13,350 --> 00:23:14,852
♪ The truth ♪

472
00:23:14,852 --> 00:23:18,147
♪ The truth, the truth
shall set you free ♪

473
00:23:18,147 --> 00:23:42,463
♪

474
00:23:46,884 --> 00:23:50,220
Akira and Agito are really
starting to let loose.

475
00:23:50,220 --> 00:23:52,014
Their two Fangs are colliding.

476
00:23:52,014 --> 00:23:53,766
But in the midst of
all these attacks,

477
00:23:53,766 --> 00:23:55,392
I feel like their hearts
are being wounded too.

478
00:23:55,392 --> 00:23:57,227
Agito, the wind
is still blowing.

479
00:23:57,227 --> 00:24:00,022
The God of Wind hasn't turned
his back on us just yet.

480
00:24:00,022 --> 00:24:01,899
Let me ride your Fang!

481
00:24:01,899 --> 00:24:03,400
This is the Wing Road.

482
00:24:03,400 --> 00:24:05,235
Ikki's spreading his wings!

483
00:24:05,235 --> 00:24:06,445
Next time on <i>Air Gear,</i>

484
00:24:06,445 --> 00:24:08,072
the Behemoth and
the Great White Shark

485
00:24:08,072 --> 00:24:09,573
face off one last time,

486
00:24:09,573 --> 00:24:12,534
and there can only be
one King of the Beasts!

487
00:24:12,534 --> 00:24:14,578
♪

